---
/**
 * rest-api/0002 · Figure 4 — "status-code families at a glance".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/rest-api/lessons/0002-http-methods-and-status-codes.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the
 * MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes. No arrowhead markers are referenced here.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 230"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Status code families: 2xx success, 3xx redirection, 4xx client error, 5xx server error, each with key codes"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="300"
                y="16"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">STATUS-CODE FAMILIES AT A GLANCE</text
            >
            <!-- 2xx -->
            <rect
                x="14"
                y="28"
                width="280"
                height="92"
                rx="9"
                fill="#eef5ee"
                stroke="#2f5d3a"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text x="28" y="48" font-size="13" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a">2xx · Success</text>
            <text x="28" y="68" font-size="9.5" fill="#244a2e">200 OK — success with a body</text>
            <text x="28" y="83" font-size="9.5" fill="#244a2e"
                >201 Created — MUST add Location header</text
            >
            <text x="28" y="98" font-size="9.5" fill="#244a2e"
                >202 Accepted — async, not done yet</text
            >
            <text x="28" y="113" font-size="9.5" fill="#244a2e"
                >204 No Content — success, empty body</text
            >
            <!-- 3xx -->
            <rect
                x="306"
                y="28"
                width="280"
                height="92"
                rx="9"
                fill="#eef2f5"
                stroke="#1f3a5a"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text x="320" y="48" font-size="13" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >3xx · Redirection</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="68" font-size="9.5" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >301/308 permanent · 302/307 temporary</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="83" font-size="9.5" fill="#1f3a5a">307/308 preserve method + body</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="98" font-size="9.5" fill="#1f3a5a">301/302 may switch POST → GET</text>
            <text x="320" y="113" font-size="9.5" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >304 Not Modified — a feature, not error</text
            >
            <!-- 4xx -->
            <rect
                x="14"
                y="128"
                width="280"
                height="92"
                rx="9"
                fill="#f7ecea"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text x="28" y="148" font-size="13" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
                >4xx · Client error</text
            >
            <text x="28" y="168" font-size="9.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >400 malformed · 422 well-formed, invalid</text
            >
            <text x="28" y="183" font-size="9.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >401 who are you? · 403 not allowed</text
            >
            <text x="28" y="198" font-size="9.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >404 hidden/absent · 410 gone · 409 conflict</text
            >
            <text x="28" y="213" font-size="9.5" fill="#7a2218">405 +Allow · 429 +Retry-After</text>
            <!-- 5xx -->
            <rect
                x="306"
                y="128"
                width="280"
                height="92"
                rx="9"
                fill="#fbfaf2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text x="320" y="148" font-size="13" font-weight="700" fill="#7a1f12"
                >5xx · Server error</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="168" font-size="9.5" fill="#2c2a26">500 generic · 502 bad gateway</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="183" font-size="9.5" fill="#2c2a26"
                >503 unavailable (+Retry-After)</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="198" font-size="9.5" fill="#2c2a26">504 gateway timeout</text>
            <text x="320" y="213" font-size="9.5" fill="#9a2417"
                >Never 5xx for a client's bad input</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The cardinal anti-pattern: returning <code>200</code> with an error embedded in the body.
        <strong>Don't tunnel errors through success.</strong>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
